            <h3>Stream Now on... Nowhere</h3>
            <p>Initially released on Cartoon Network, Infinity Train soon became an HBO Max Original in August of 2020 with the release of its third book.
                But this didn't last long as the show was cancelled less than a year later in April of 2021. 
                While this meant that there wouldn't be any new episodes the show could still be streamed on the service.
                That was, until it was quietly removed in August of 2022 to the dismay of fans.</p>
            <p>"[...] Cartoon Network warned them not to do this as it would hurt relationships with creators and talent, 
                but they clearly do not care what any of this looks like publicly, much less about how we feel about it." <i>-Owen Dennis</i></p>
            <a href="https://owendennis.substack.com/p/so-uh-whats-going-on-with-infinity" target="_blank">Read the full article here</a>
        </div>
