            <h3>Why was Infinity Train canceled?</h3>
            <p>Infinity Train was canceled shortly after Book 4 premiered, a direct result of the Warner Brothers-Discovery merger and subsequent restructuring. The reasoning was particularly frustrating: executives believed children couldn't relate to the planned Book 5 protagonist, an adult character named Amelia. While the show was aimed at a younger demographic, it had a notable appeal to all ages—an audience studios often struggle to acknowledge.</p>
